data.chText: 旅行拖车，宿营拖车（无发动机，由其他车拖动，多供度假时住宿用）
data.enText: a road vehicle without an engine that is pulled by a car, designed for people to live and sleep in, especially when they are on holiday/vacation

data.chText: （供居住用的）有篷马车，大篷车
data.enText: a covered vehicle that is pulled by a horse and used for living in

data.chText: （尤指穿越沙漠的）旅行队，车队
data.enText: a group of people with vehicles or animals who are travelling together, especially across the desert

means: 宿营拖车(无发动机，由其他车拖动，多供度假时住宿用)

tr: a camper equipped with living quarters
a procession (of wagons or mules or camels) traveling together in single file
example: we were part of a caravan of almost a thousand camels
they joined the wagon train for safety

value.def: A caravan is a vehicle without an engine that can be pulled by a car or van. It contains beds and cooking equipment so that people can live or spend their holidays in it.

value.boxr_value: in AM, usually use 美国英语通常用 trailer

value.def: A caravan is a group of people and animals or vehicles who travel together.

example.ex: ...the old caravan routes from Central Asia to China.
example.tran: 从中亚到中国的古老的旅行线路

value.tran: (带着牲口的一群人结伴而行的)旅行队;车队
